trans-unit.source: Module Overview
trans-unit.target: Module Overview

trans-unit.source: You can use the <ui>Enter Data</ui> module to create small datasets by typing values, rather than loading data from a source in Azure Machine Learning Studio or from a local file.
trans-unit.target: You can use the <ui>Enter Data</ui> module to create small datasets by typing values, rather than loading data from a source in Azure Machine Learning Studio or from a local file.

trans-unit.source: How to Use Enter Data
trans-unit.target: How to Use Enter Data

trans-unit.source: To create new data for use in experiments
trans-unit.target: To create new data for use in experiments

trans-unit.source: Click inside the <ui>Data</ui> text box to start entering data.
trans-unit.target: Click inside the <ui>Data</ui> text box to start entering data.

trans-unit.source: The column headings can be typed in the first row.
trans-unit.target: The column headings can be typed in the first row.

trans-unit.source: If you don’t type heading names, the first row of values will be used as the column headings.
trans-unit.target: If you don’t type heading names, the first row of values will be used as the column headings.

trans-unit.source: Press ENTER after each row.
trans-unit.target: Press ENTER after each row.

trans-unit.source: Be sure to press ENTER after the final row.
trans-unit.target: Be sure to press ENTER after the final row.

trans-unit.source: However, if you press ENTER multiple times, the final empty row will be trimmed, but other empty rows will be treated as missing values.
trans-unit.target: However, if you press ENTER multiple times, the final empty row will be trimmed, but other empty rows will be treated as missing values.

trans-unit.source: You can also paste data into <ui>Enter Data</ui>, or copy and paste between instances of <ui>Enter Data</ui>.
trans-unit.target: You can also paste data into <ui>Enter Data</ui>, or copy and paste between instances of <ui>Enter Data</ui>.

trans-unit.source: Choose the data format to use for persisting the data.
trans-unit.target: Choose the data format to use for persisting the data.

trans-unit.source: Data
trans-unit.target: Data

trans-unit.source: The <ui>Data</ui> text box provides a single column with line numbers where you can type values.
trans-unit.target: The <ui>Data</ui> text box provides a single column with line numbers where you can type values.

trans-unit.source: Press ENTER to start a new line.
trans-unit.target: Press ENTER to start a new line.

trans-unit.source: You can enter rows with missing values, and then add values later.
trans-unit.target: You can enter rows with missing values, and then add values later.

trans-unit.source: After you have run the experiment, you can see the dataset by clicking the output port and selecting <ui>Visualize</ui>.
trans-unit.target: After you have run the experiment, you can see the dataset by clicking the output port and selecting <ui>Visualize</ui>.

trans-unit.source: Technical Notes
trans-unit.target: Technical Notes

trans-unit.source: Regardless of the saved format, data that you enter is implicitly converted to the dataset (<link xlink:href="285668ca-bd74-42b2-9c2c-3111b4819e56" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">DataTable</link>) format for use in experiments.
trans-unit.target: Regardless of the saved format, data that you enter is implicitly converted to the dataset (<link xlink:href="285668ca-bd74-42b2-9c2c-3111b4819e56" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">DataTable</link>) format for use in experiments.

trans-unit.source: However, data is not persisted as a saved dataset unless you explicitly save the output.
trans-unit.target: However, data is not persisted as a saved dataset unless you explicitly save the output.

trans-unit.source: If you do not save the data in <ui>Enter Data</ui> as a dataset, it will be removed from the workspace cache when you end the session.
trans-unit.target: If you do not save the data in <ui>Enter Data</ui> as a dataset, it will be removed from the workspace cache when you end the session.

trans-unit.source: However, you can run the experiment again to make the data available.
trans-unit.target: However, you can run the experiment again to make the data available.

trans-unit.source: If you combine the data from <ui>Enter Data</ui> with another dataset, the combined dataset cannot have two columns with the same name.
trans-unit.target: If you combine the data from <ui>Enter Data</ui> with another dataset, the combined dataset cannot have two columns with the same name.

trans-unit.source: If there are duplicate column names, a numeric suffix is appended to the column from the right dataset to make the column names unique.
trans-unit.target: If there are duplicate column names, a numeric suffix is appended to the column from the right dataset to make the column names unique.

trans-unit.source: For example, assume that you have two instances of <ui>Enter Data</ui> that contain the column <userInputLocalizable>TestData</userInputLocalizable>, and use the <link xlink:href="5714a225-befd-438a-9bb5-f6fdc50a4efb" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Add Columns</link> module to merge them.
trans-unit.target: For example, assume that you have two instances of <ui>Enter Data</ui> that contain the column <userInputLocalizable>TestData</userInputLocalizable>, and use the <link xlink:href="5714a225-befd-438a-9bb5-f6fdc50a4efb" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Add Columns</link> module to merge them.

trans-unit.source: The column from the left instance of <ui>Enter Data</ui> would remain as <userInputLocalizable>TestData</userInputLocalizable>, and the column from the right instance of <ui>Enter Data</ui> would be renamed <userInputLocalizable>TestData (2)</userInputLocalizable>.
trans-unit.target: The column from the left instance of <ui>Enter Data</ui> would remain as <userInputLocalizable>TestData</userInputLocalizable>, and the column from the right instance of <ui>Enter Data</ui> would be renamed <userInputLocalizable>TestData (2)</userInputLocalizable>.
